      <title>Crash bug when searching /barter</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=13888#M13888</link>
      <description>This bug has been confirmed on three computers.&amp;nbsp; Two belonged to me, one belongs to a friend.&amp;nbsp; All three use very different UI's.&amp;nbsp; In each case, it causes EQ to immediately crash to desktop.&amp;nbsp; This is a repeatable bug.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Procedure:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;1. Enter the bazaar.&lt;br&gt;2. Type "/barter" to bring up the search window.&lt;br&gt;3. Enter any search string in the Search box at the bottom.&lt;br&gt;4. Press the Search button or hit Enter on your keyboard.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Result:&lt;br&gt;If the search returns zero results, you get an appropriate message and nothing unusual happens.&amp;nbsp; If the search would return one or more results, EQ immediately crashes to the desktop.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Expected result:&lt;br&gt;EQ does not crash.&amp;nbsp; The barter window displays a list of results.&lt;br&gt;</description>
