      <title>Re: Crash bug when searching /barter</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=13901#M13901</link>
      <description>Yes and no.&amp;nbsp; Sony's not responsible for custom UI maintenance, it's true, but a faulty UI (whether due to a patch or just badly written by the author) shouldn't cause a crash to desktop; it should just cause the client to report a bad UI and load the default UI, either for that window or for the whole UI.&amp;nbsp; In the past, Sony used to note prominently which UI files changed with a patch; nowadays, it's a much briefer note.&amp;nbsp; Here's all the patch message said about the Barter window:&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;- The default size for the barter and bazaar windows has been increased.&lt;br&gt;- You can now filter the barter window by seller name.&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;The first line should have no effect on custom UI's, and the second didn't suggest that using a custom barter UI would cause your client to crash ...&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anywho, that's all moot.&amp;nbsp; We know what the problem is now, so we can act to avoid it or (in the case of custom UI writers) fix it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here's a different problem.&amp;nbsp; This time I'm using the default UI.&amp;nbsp; Short version: searching for a specific buyer's lines doesn't work.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Procedure:&lt;br&gt;1. Enter the bazaar.&lt;br&gt;2. Type "/barter" to bring up the barter search window.&lt;br&gt;3. Select a buyer from the name drop-down list.&lt;br&gt;4. Press the search button.&amp;nbsp; (Note that the box for typing in an item name is blank.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Results:&lt;br&gt;Approximately half the time, you will get back buy lines from an incorrect buyer (not the one you selected) or from more than one buyer.&amp;nbsp; Every time, without exception, you will get yellow text stating "Your search found too many results, some are not displayed."&amp;nbsp; This search also processes slower than a search that specifies (part of) an item name.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Expected results:&lt;br&gt;The list displays all buy lines from the selected buyer.&amp;nbsp; Since the limit on the number of buy lines that a player can set is lower than the limit on returned buy lines when searching (which should be 200, as of before this last patch), the person searching should always see all the listed buyer's buylines.&amp;nbsp; The yellow text message indicating too many results never appears.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
